# ============================================================================
# PROJECT SPECIFIC
# ============================================================================

# Keep example/template files but ignore actual data files
!.claude/skills/*/config.example.json
config.local.json

# Ignore skill outputs but keep skill code
.claude/skills/*/output/
.claude/skills/*/tmp/

# Keep README and documentation
!README.md
!*.md

# But ignore generated reports with personal data
summary_report.md
gap_analysis_report.md
interview_questions_*.md

# ============================================================================
# WHAT TO COMMIT (Explicitly allowed)
# ============================================================================

# These files SHOULD be committed:
# - .claude/skills/**/*.py (Python scripts)
# - .claude/skills/**/*.md (Documentation, but NOT output reports)
# - .claude/skills/**/SKILL.md (Skill definitions)
# - .claude/skills/**/references/*.md (Reference documentation)
# - .claude/command/*.md (Command definitions)
# - config.json (if it doesn't contain personal data)
# - .gitignore (this file)
# - README.md
# - LICENSE

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================

# To share your skill with others:
# 1. Remove all personal data from config.json
# 2. Create config.example.json with placeholder values
# 3. Ensure no resume files or job data are included
# 4. Test the skill with sample data
# 5. Document any required setup in README.md

# To use this project:
# 1. Clone the repository
# 2. Copy config.example.json to config.json
# 3. Update config.json with your personal paths
# 4. Place your resume in the resume/ directory
# 5. Run the workflow
